# Enforce Invariants at the Boundary

When a **collection** has rules (e.g. "only these items are allowed"), enforce
them at the **boundary** — the method that changes the collection.

Override `append` (or the relevant mutator) so that the rule is applied in one
place. Callers cannot add an invalid item; the collection protects itself.
The invariant is then visible and consistent. Example: `Params` overrides
`append` to respect `_ignore` and param kind; only valid params enter the list.

Do not scatter checks at every call site. One gate, one rule.
